HEADWORD: Diploma
<hw>Di*plo"ma</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Diplomas</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L., fr. Gr. <?/, fr. <?/
to double, fr. <grk>diplo`os</grk> twofold. See <er>Double</er>.]</ety>
<def>A letter or writing, usually under seal, conferring some privilege,
honor, or power; a document bearing record of a degree conferred by a
literary society or educational institution.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Diplomacy</ent>⟦br⟧
